âœ… 1. Manual Commands (Windows PowerShell)

These are the ONLY commands needed for Minikube + Nginx deployment + scaling.

Start Minikube
minikube start

Create Deployment
kubectl create deployment mynginx --image=nginx

If deployment already exists (update image)
kubectl set image deployment/mynginx nginx=nginx:latest

Check Deployment & Pods
kubectl get deployments
kubectl get pods
kubectl describe pods

Expose Deployment as a Service
kubectl expose deployment mynginx --type=NodePort --port=80 --target-port=80

Scale Pods (to 4 replicas)
kubectl scale deployment mynginx --replicas=4

Check Service
kubectl get service mynginx

Port Forward to Access Nginx
kubectl port-forward svc/mynginx 8081:80


Then open:

http://localhost:8081
